						<p>c. 8th Century.</p>						

						<p>Kōdai Mayindaṉ gifted 220 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of rice for feeding 110 Brāhmaṇas on the day of Tiruvādirai festival of the god Kuṉṟākkuḍittēvar. This he did for the merit of Mayindaṇ Vīrakāḍayaṉ.</p>						

